The paper discusses the history of metaheuristics, which are optimization algorithms that can be applied to a wide range of problems. This makes it likely to be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which are sub-categories that deal with optimization and search algorithms. Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it discusses the development of algorithms over time. The paper also touches on the use of metaheuristics in various fields, such as robotics and control systems, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
